MySQL

MySQL is an open-source Relational Database Management System (RDBMS) that stores data in tables (rows and columns) and uses SQL (Structured Query Language) to manage data.

MySQL is widely used for web applications and enterprise systems.

Simple Definition

MySQL is an open-source RDBMS that stores data in tables and allows users to create, retrieve, update, and delete data using SQL.

Features of MySQL

✔ Open-source (free to use)
✔ Uses SQL language
✔ High performance
✔ Secure (user authentication & privileges)
✔ Supports multi-user access
✔ Supports large databases

Where is MySQL Used?

MySQL is commonly used in:

Websites
E-commerce systems
Banking systems
Student management systems
Many websites built with:
WordPress
PHP
use MySQL as their database.

Basic MySQL Commands

Here are common SQL commands used in MySQL:

CREATE → Create database or table
INSERT → Add data
SELECT → Retrieve data
UPDATE → Modify data
DELETE → Remove data

Example:
SELECT * FROM Students;

Advantages of MySQL

✔ Easy to learn
✔ Reliable and stable
✔ Fast data processing
✔ Good community support
✔ Works on Windows, Linux, macOS

